  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6, then boil a kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>linguine</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>linguine</strong> for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>linguine</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/truffled-mushroom-linguine-with-garlic-bread/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, reboil a kettle</p><p>Remove 20g <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> from the fridge to soften</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, crumble and tear (or chop) the <strong>portobello</strong> and <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> into the pan</p><p>Cook for 6-7 min or until caramelised</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/truffled-mushroom-linguine-with-garlic-bread/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the mushrooms are caramelising, chop the <strong>parsley</strong>, including the stems, very finely</p><p>Peel and grate (or finely chop) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Carefully cut the <strong>ciabatta<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into 6-8 slices, without going all the way through the base</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/truffled-mushroom-linguine-with-garlic-bread/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Mash the <strong>softened</strong> <strong>butter</strong> with the <strong>grated garlic</strong>, <strong>parsley</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your<strong> garlic butter</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/truffled-mushroom-linguine-with-garlic-bread/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Line a baking tray with <strong>tin foil</strong></p><p>Spread the <strong>garlic butter</strong> between the slices of ciabatta then add the <strong>sliced ciabatta</strong> to the tray</p><p>Sprinkle with a 1/3 of the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 5-6 min or until the cheese is starting to brown - this is your <strong>garlic bread</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/truffled-mushroom-linguine-with-garlic-bread/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the garlic bread is cooking, dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once the mushrooms have caramelised, add the <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> to the pan and cook for 30 secs, then add the <strong>vegetable stock</strong></p><p>Cook for 4-5 min or until reduced to a pasta sauce-like consistency</p><p>Stir through the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and the <strong>creme fraiche</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/truffled-mushroom-linguine-with-garlic-bread/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained linguine</strong> to the sauce and give everything a good old mix up – this is your <strong>mushroom linguine</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p><p>Wash the <strong>rocket</strong> and pat it dry with <strong>kitchen paper</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/truffled-mushroom-linguine-with-garlic-bread/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>mushroom linguine</strong> in bowls and top with the <strong>rocket</strong></p><p>Drizzle with the<strong> truffle flavoured extra virgin olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
